Jos – Benue Rebirth Movement (BRM) leaders have barred ldoma sons and daughters from accepting to serve as running mates to Tiv governorship aspirants in all the political parties in the 2023. Addressing newsmen in Jos on Wednesday on behalf of Idoma Leaders of Thought, Elder Statesman General, Geofrey Ejiga, said since Benue State was created in 1976, almost half a century ago, Idoma people of Benue-South Senatorial Zone have not been given opportunity to produce the state governor or Speaker of the House of Assembly, Head of Judiciary, Vice Chancellor, Benue State University or Vice Chancellor of Federal University of Agriculture, Makurdi. According to him, “Indeed Idoma people cannot head any key office in the state.” Ejiga said that they had agreementof zoningof political offices in Benue in 1998 agreed on by the current political leaders in the state, adding that it was agreed that the governorship position will rotate among the three senatorial zones in Benue and as a result of that the Tiv people of zone A and B have produced Ex governor Akume and governor Gabriel Suswan. -Advertisement- He lamented that after Suswan, the governorship should have gone to the Idoma people of Benue-South, but regrettably the ticket went to Governor Ortom.